  <li id="comment-40624" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/13211454867526009485" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Andi</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=206#comment-40624"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-02-17T17:57:35-05:00">Monday, February 17, 2014 at 5:57 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I made lots of fruit curds last summer, and I found if I blended the eggs and citrus juice with something like an immersion blender (or a regular blender if you want) before heating them, there was no chance of chunks of just egg post-cooking.  So you could keep the lime zest (and skip the straining.)</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=206#comment-40624' data-commentid="40624" data-postid="206" data-belowelement="comment-40624" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Andi" aria-label='Reply to Andi'>Reply</a>    </div>
