    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I LOVE all flavors of citrus curd.  Last year for the first time I found Seville oranges in New York City.  And guess what I made? Seville Orange Curd (from Nigella&#39;s How to Eat)?  It was spectacular.  I made Clotide&#39;s Piège Cake and served it with a teeny bit of loosely whipped cream flavored with Mathide Orange XO Liqueur and the curd.  It was spectacular!</p>
<p>Your mother&#39;s curd served with those little cookies sounds delightful.  I&#39;m heading for the store in a little while so I can snag all the ingredients and make them.  Thanks.</p>
