  <li id="comment-40668" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/11201197904119497027" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">pinkbuttercream</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=206#comment-40668"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-02-18T14:12:06-05:00">Tuesday, February 18, 2014 at 2:12 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>A trick I picked up along the way was to reserve half the zest and add it to the curd post cooking and straining. This way the zest in the curd is bright and uncooked, it looks prettier, and tastes great (plus no lumps!)</p>
    </div>

